T1  - Editors' Note: Streamlining the Revise and Resubmit Process at AMJ
Y1  - 2006/10/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2006.22798161
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2006.22798161
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 873
EP  - 874
VL  - 49
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the process in which authors revise and resubmit their works to the ?Academy of Management Journal? and how it is working on simplifying the process. Many are concerned that authors try to respond to all of a reviewer's comments and, thus, the overall quality of the article drops. Because of this, the journal will no longer ask authors to respond to every comment they receive, but rather spend more time revising their manuscripts so that it becomes a more cohesive work. There must be communication between reviewers, editors, and authors, as well, so that each party understands what components are most crucial to a quality issue.
AB  - The article discusses the process in which authors revise and resubmit their works to the ?Academy of Management Journal? and how it is working on simplifying the process. Many are concerned that authors try to respond to all of a reviewer's comments and, thus, the overall quality of the article drops. Because of this, the journal will no longer ask authors to respond to every comment they receive, but rather spend more time revising their manuscripts so that it becomes a more cohesive work. There must be communication between reviewers, editors, and authors, as well, so that each party understands what components are most crucial to a quality issue.
